**Summary:**
The `PhotoCollage` card is a card that displays a collage of photos with captions and supports a dark mode toggle. The card has a title and a grid of photo items, each with a URL, caption, and alt text.

**Import:**
```
import { PhotoCollage } from '../photo-collage-minimalist-photography-collection-cd58a3f7-762f-4459-ba33-77ae7c2b8b5b/photo-collage/photo-collage';
```

**Usage as a Field:**
To use the `PhotoCollage` card as a field within a consuming card or field, you can define a field of type `PhotoCollage` and use the `@fields.photoCollage` syntax to display it:

```gts
@field photoCollage = contains(PhotoCollage);
```

**Template Usage:**
Inside a consuming card or field, you can use the `PhotoCollage` card by rendering the `@fields.photoCollage` component and passing in the necessary data:

```hbs
<@fields.photoCollage
  @model={{this.photoCollageData}}
  @format={{this.format}}
/>
```

In this example, `this.photoCollageData` is an instance of the `PhotoCollage` card, and `this.format` specifies the display format (e.g., `isolated`, `embedded`).
